reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 25, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars It's not missing a knife
reviews.reviewText: I read the reviews prior to purchasing and I was a bit concerned about the multiple complaints about a missing steak knife. I really loved the black set so I figured, I would just contact Amazon or the company if there was anything missing. After receiving and putting the knives in the correct slots, I thought I was missing a knife too, but I wasn't. And I'm almost positive nobody else is missing a knife either. There are 6 steak knives in the set. 3 on the left and 3 on the right. Not 8. That 7th knife that looks like a steak knife is the tomato knife. There are 19 pieces total. THAT INCLUDES THE KNIFE HOLDER. Once you put the knives in their correct slots, there appears to be an empty slot between the steak knives and the knife sharpener. But if you put a knife in there, it will not sit right. That's not a spot for a knife. I hope this helps previous and potential buyers.The knives are beautiful. I haven't put them in the disher or let them dry in the dish rack. I wash them and immediately dry and put them back in their slot. They are very sharp. I honestly didn't realize how dull my knives were. I haven't needed to sharpen them yet but I would be concerned that the color will chip. I've had them for a few months now and only one knife has a small chip.

reviews.reviewTitle: Surprisingly sharp. Decent budget set with some quirks.
reviews.reviewText: Bought these to replace my cheap, and aging 12 piece knife set.The bigger knives I do like, and are very sharp (at least comparing it to my older crappy set). Can cut things easier now and more smoothly.However, the peeler isn't the greatest, so I don't use it. The "Cheese" knife seems gimmicky and shouldn't have even been offered. The steak knives are decent at best. Also the "block" that holds it is only ideal for really open spaces. Under a cabinet, forget it. I have 40 inch cabinets with a 36 inch height counter (8 ft ceilings) and I can't remove a knife without tipping the block over. Annoying, but your mileage may vary depending on your kitchen style.Overall for $50 it's hard to beat and they look great. It's a good knife set for budget conscious individuals or families.
